        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Rylok1</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The tree spectre is the one that spawns in the swamp area of Feerrot, the other specs spawn inside the fear cave.  It spawns next to a tree near the fear cave entrance.  The bouncers don't roam around there(at least they didn't when I was there a few months ago).  The only thing to worry about is someone training the spectres from the cave on you.  As far as tactics...  I would set up on the flat area of the hill by the spec.  Pull with Dooming Darkness, wait a couple seconds, cast your undead fear, send in pet, throw a dot or 2 on him, reapply fear when necessary and he'll drop pretty quick.  I would usually hit him with a couple undead nukes just to work on evoc skill (and kill them faster) because mana wasn't an issue for me once I got the routine down.  They don't have a lot of HP, so as long as you keep them feared, you and your pet will be fine.  Your pet will only last a few seconds going toe to toe with them, they hit very hard and fast.  Always keep an eye out for people running by, and listen for the spectre sounds, because if you get spectres trained on you, you will die before you even know what happened.  Oh yeah, the RM zone is fairly close if trouble.  Good luck  ;)</P><P>Rylok Darklyte<BR>52 Heretic<BR>Divine Blade/Lanys</P><P>Edited by - Rylok1 on 08/02/2002  09:50:17</P><P>Edited by - Rylok1 on 08/02/2002  10:08:09</font></td>
