        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> That spec can kick you ass fast if you are a little unlucky.  I did the same as you, and came back at 36.  It was much better.  Always keep your damage sink up at these low levels.  You get enough for the weapons that the gem cost should not be an issue.  I'm a DE so I could sell without zoning to the merchants.</P><P>If you get a resist, you will be getting lots of aggro.  One more resist and Goober is going to have a hard time getting the spec off your butt.</P><P>Undead slow can help.  If he resists fear, cast undead slow and your pet will be able to hang in there MUCH longer.  I'm sure it's been said before, but specs are still difficuly to handle at high levels.  They hit hard and fast.</P><P>I tired rotting him....  once.</P><P>-DV</P><P> </font></td>
