 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Talanor</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I started camping spec at 39. Tried several times at earlier levels to root/rot, and fear kite but ended up dead due to resists too many times. At 39 I changed tactics and tried again with MUCH success.</P><P>Spells to mem<BR>Shackle of Spirit<BR>Expulse Undead<BR>Drain Spirit<BR>Renew Bones<BR>Augment Death/Greater Shielding/Spirit Armor/Steelskin(Cycle as needed)<BR>Call of Bones<BR>HS<BR>FD</P><P>I camp at top of hill. Park pet buff up, and augment pet. Pull with Shackle from back edge of hill. If it is resisted the first time it will cycle just in time to recast when the spec gets to top of hill and meets your pet.(always let spec get to top of hill before sending pet to avoid aggroing the tunnel specs) It is almost never resisted more than once. Pause a few seconds between casts so pet holds aggro, drain spirit to regain life lost to call, then use undead dd. Pause to heal pet as needed. Using this technique about the only time I have problems anymore is if I get adds. The combination of -50% attack speed on the spec, and +50% attack speed on pet allows level 39 pet to tank specs pretty effectively. Some pulls my pet manages to survive without having to be healed, at most I renew him 2 times durig a fight.</P><P></P><P>Talanor S'Tox<BR>Dark Elf Necromancer<BR>Sinister Undertones<BR>Seventh Hammer<BR>Profile: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117251" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117251</a></P><P>Tazuuk<BR>Iksar Necromancer<BR>Sullon Zek<BR>Profile: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116028" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116028</a></font></td>
