        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> That is great IF you have sow/jboots. At 40 I have still not managed to get jboots, and can't always afford a supply of sow potions. Without them I got raped by the spec until I hit 39 tried my own thing.I figure someone else has used same tactic, but I "discovered" my method through good old fashioned trial and error. My method may not be the most mana efficient, but I find that dropping the spectre without taking a single hit is worth it. I also have just enough time between pops to get fm about 30-45 seconds before the next pop. And I dunno if they changed regen rates on our pets but even if my pet is pounded down to 20% of his life he is still back to full before the next pop. IMO running all over the place with pissed off spec chasing is too risky, I would rather keep the spec in one spot while my pet and I kill him. Just my 2 cents though.</P><P></P><P>Talanor S'Tox<BR>Dark Elf Necromancer<BR>Sinister Undertones<BR>Seventh Hammer<BR>Profile: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117251" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117251</a></P><P>Tazuuk<BR>Iksar Necromancer<BR>Sullon Zek<BR>Profile: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116028" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116028</a></font></td>
