        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I started camping the Tree spec at level 35 and ended up getting tired of him at 39 and headed to the Mines of Nurga. The Tree spec was a breeze as long as no inconsiderate high leveled player didn't rustle up the cave specs onto me. In the time I was camping the Tree spec I racked in easily 1k+ in coin and lots of research words. I found it easy to just stand down hill from the spec and cast Dooming Darkness, run back a little and cast Torment of the Eternities, sick pet, immediately nuke with Torbas Acid Blast to keep the agroo, and just walk the spec away from the hill, every now and then I would stop to either Spirit tap it or Torbas Acid Blast it again, all the while my pet would beat it silly from behind.I never had any mana issues since I had plenty of time to med it back before the next pop.</P><P>At level 36 I was worried that I wasn't getting enough xp and wanted the added thrill so I was just doing the same steps but without my pet. Every once in awhile things would go wrong and there would be an add so if my undead fear failed or Feign Death failed I usually was slain due to the fact that I usually was way too overweighted from all those scythes to be running from multiple spectres. But still the Tree spec yielded the best XP I have ever recieved.</P><P><BR>Vaylain Zek`Bressen - 39 Dark Elf Necromancer<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=299227" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=299227</a></P><P>Azeccia Battlebow - 42 Ranger<BR>Aquen Beastsummoner - 36 Beastlord</P><P></P><P>Edited by - azeccia on 08/21/2002  14:53:27</font></td>
